The surface morphology of the 3wt% Er/BiOBr was examined by scanning electron microscopy. It can be seen that sphere-like Er/BiOBr hierarchical structures are formed with an average diameter of 2–3μm (Fig. 3
                        a). The high-magnification SEM images is shown in Fig. 3b. The as-prepared composites were self-assembled generated by irregular BiOBr nanosheets. The EDS analysis suggests 3wt% Er/BiOBr microspheres only contain the elements of Bi, O, Br and Er (Fig. 3c). From the EDS mapping (Fig. 4
                        ), it can be found the elements Er, Bi, O and Br evenly distributed in 3wt% Er/BiOBr materials. This result further proves that the as-prepared samples are Er/BiOBr composite materials, which is consistent with the results of XPS analysis.
